desc: Returns true if automation is allowed to insert the given stack (ignoring stack size) into the given slot.

name: getTntPlacedBy
desc: returns null or the entityliving it was placed or ignited by

name: createMinecart
desc: Creates a new minecart of the specified type in the specified location in the given world. par0World - world to create the minecart in, double par1,par3,par5 represent x,y,z respectively. int par7 specifies the type: 1 for MinecartChest, 2 for MinecartFurnace, 3 for MinecartTNT, 4 for MinecartMobSpawner, 5 for MinecartHopper and 0 for a standard empty minecart

name: explodeCart
desc: Makes the minecart explode.

name: ignite
desc: Ignites this TNT cart.

name: getAccessibleSlotsFromSide
desc: Returns an array containing the indices of the slots that can be accessed by automation on the given side of this block.

name: getAllStitchSlots
desc: Gets the slot and all its subslots

name: getMinV
desc: Returns the minimum V coordinate to use when rendering with this icon.

name: getInterpolatedV
desc: Gets a V coordinate on the icon. 0 returns vMin and 16 returns vMax. Other arguments return in-between values.

name: getMinU
desc: Returns the minimum U coordinate to use when rendering with this icon.

name: getMaxV
desc: Returns the maximum V coordinate to use when rendering with this icon.

name: getIconWidth
desc: Returns the width of the icon, in pixels.

name: getMaxU
desc: Returns the maximum U coordinate to use when rendering with this icon.

name: getInterpolatedU
desc: Gets a U coordinate on the icon. 0 returns uMin and 16 returns uMax. Other arguments return in-between values.

name: getIconHeight
desc: Returns the height of the icon, in pixels.

name: updateCompass
desc: Updates the compass based on the given x,z coords and camera direction

name: allocateSlot
desc: Attempts to find space for specified tile

name: expandAndAllocateSlot
desc: Expand stitched texture in order to make space for specified tile

name: canTranslate
desc: Determines whether or not translateToLocal will find a translation for the given key.

name: canDragIntoSlot
desc: Returns true if the player can "drag-spilt" items into this slot,. returns true by default. Called to check if the slot can be added to a list of Slots to split the held ItemStack across.

name: getDamageSrc
desc: Get the DamageSource of the CombatEntry instance.

name: getIndirectPowerOutput
desc: Returns the indirect signal strength being outputted by the given block in the *opposite* of the given direction. Args: X, Y, Z, direction

name: getBlockPowerInput
desc: Returns the highest redstone signal strength powering the given block. Args: X, Y, Z.

name: getItemIconForUseDuration
desc: used to cycle through icons based on their used duration, i.e. for the bow

name: getExplosivePlacedBy
desc: Returns either the entity that placed the explosive block, the entity that caused the explosion or null.

name: getSpriteNumber
desc: Returns 0 for /terrain.png, 1 for /gui/items.png

name: setMinecartName
desc: Sets the minecart's name.

name: onActivatorRailPass
desc: Called every tick the minecart is on an activator rail. Args: x, y, z, is the rail receiving power

name: isIgnited
desc: Returns true if the TNT minecart is ignited.

name: getXPos
desc: Gets the world X position for this hopper entity.

name: getZPos
desc: Gets the world Z position for this hopper entity.

name: getYPos
desc: Gets the world Y position for this hopper entity.

name: setBlocked
desc: Set whether this hopper minecart is being blocked by an activator rail.

name: getBlocked
desc: Get whether this hopper minecart is being blocked by an activator rail.

name: isBlockProtected
desc: Returns true if a player does not have permission to edit the block at the given coordinates.

name: getValidValues
desc: Gets all the valid values. Args: @param par0: Whether or not to include color values. @param par1: Whether or not to include fancy-styling values (anything that isn't a color value or the "reset" value).

name: getFriendlyName
desc: Gets the friendly name of this value.

name: getFormattingCode
desc: Gets the formatting code that produces this format.

name: getValueByName
desc: Gets a value by its friendly name; null if the given name does not map to a defined value.

name: isFancyStyling
desc: False if this is just changing the color or resetting; true otherwise.

name: isColor
desc: Checks if typo is a color.

name: joinNiceStringFromCollection
desc: Creates a linguistic series joining together the elements of the given collection.  Examples: 1) {} --> "",  2) {"Steve"} --> "Steve",  3) {"Steve", "Phil"} --> "Steve and Phil",  4) {"Steve", "Phil", "Mark"} --> "Steve, Phil and Mark"

name: getTeam
desc: Retrieve the ScorePlayerTeam instance identified by the passed team name

name: getPlayersTeam
desc: Gets the ScorePlayerTeam object for the given username.

name: removeTeam
desc: Removes the team from the scoreboard, updates all player memberships and broadcasts the deletion to all players

name: removePlayerFromTeam
desc: Removes the given username from the given ScorePlayerTeam. If the player is not on the team then an IllegalStateException is thrown.

name: getObjectiveDisplaySlot
desc: Returns 'list' for 0, 'sidebar' for 1, 'belowName for 2, otherwise null.

name: getObjective
desc: Returns a ScoreObjective for the objective name

name: getTeams
desc: Retrieve all registered ScorePlayerTeam instances

name: createTeam
desc: Verifies that the given name doesn't already refer to an existing team, creates it otherwise and broadcasts the addition to all players

name: getTeamNames
desc: Retrieve all registered ScorePlayerTeam names

name: getObjectiveDisplaySlotNumber
desc: Returns 0 for (case-insensitive) 'list', 1 for 'sidebar', 2 for 'belowName', otherwise -1.

name: attemptDamageItem
desc: Attempts to damage the ItemStack with par1 amount of damage, If the ItemStack has the Unbreaking enchantment there is a chance for each point of damage to be negated. Returns true if it takes more damage than getMaxDamage(). Returns false otherwise or if the ItemStack can't be damaged or if all points of damage are negated.

name: getRegisteredName
desc: Retrieve the name by which this team is registered in the scoreboard

name: getColorSuffix
desc: Returns the color suffix for the player's team name

name: formatPlayerName
desc: Returns the player name including the color prefixes and suffixes

name: getColorPrefix
desc: Returns the color prefix for the player's team name

name: isInvisibleToPlayer
desc: Only used by renderer in EntityLivingBase subclasses.\nDetermines if an entity is visible or not to a specfic player, if the entity is normally invisible.\nFor EntityLivingBase subclasses, returning false when invisible will render the entity semitransparent.

name: writeMountToNBT
desc: Like writeToNBTOptional but does not check if the entity is ridden. Used for saving ridden entities with their riders.

name: setTransferTicker
desc: Sets the transfer ticker, used to determine the delay between transfers.

name: canTransfer
desc: Returns whether the hopper cart can currently transfer an item.

name: setScaleForAge
desc: "Sets the scale for an ageable entity according to the boolean parameter, which says if it's a child."

name: setDelayToMin
desc: Sets the delay to minDelay if parameter given is 1, else return false.

name: getEntityNameToSpawn
desc: Gets the entity name that should be spawned.

name: canRun
desc: Returns true if there's a player close enough to this mob spawner to activate it.

name: canInsertItem
desc: Returns true if automation can insert the given item in the given slot from the given side. Args: Slot, item, side

name: canExtractItem
desc: Returns true if automation can extract the given item in the given slot from the given side. Args: Slot, item, side

name: saveExtraData
desc: Save extra data not associated with any Chunk.  Not saved during autosave, only during world unload.  Currently unimplemented.

name: saveChunkData
desc: saves chunk data - currently only called during execution of the Save All command

name: onBroken
desc: Called when this entity is broken. Entity parameter may be null.

name: removeFrameFromMap
desc: Removes the dot representing this frame's position from the map when the item frame is broken.

name: dismountEntity
desc: Moves the entity to a position out of the way of its mount.

name: updateLeashedState
desc: Applies logic related to leashes, for example dragging the entity or breaking the leash.

name: clearLeashed
desc: Removes the leash from this entity. Second parameter tells whether to send a packet to surrounding players.

name: setLeashedToEntity
getHomePosition
desc: Returns the chunk coordinate object of the home position.

name: hasHome
desc: Returns whether a home area is defined for this entity.

name: addGrowth
desc: "Adds the value of the parameter times 20 to the age of this entity. If the entity is an adult (if the entity's age is greater than 0), it will have no effect."

name: getHorseArmorIndex
desc: 0 = iron, 1 = gold, 2 = diamond

name: getHorseType
desc: returns the horse type

name: parseDoubleBounded
desc: Parses a double from the given string.  Throws if the string could not be parsed as a double, or if it's not between the given min and max values.

name: parseBoolean
desc: Parses a boolean value from the given string.  Throws if the string does not contain a boolean value.  Accepted values are (case-sensitive): "true", "false", "0", "1".

name: parseDoubleWithMin
desc: Parses a double from the given string.  Throws if the string could not be parsed as a double, or if it's less than the given minimum value.

name: getAttribute
desc: Get the Attribute this is an instance of

name: getModifier
desc: Returns attribute modifier, if any, by the given UUID

name: registerAttribute
desc: Registers an attribute with this AttributeMap, returns a modifiable AttributeInstance associated with this map

name: isSaved
desc: @see #isSaved

name: setSaved
desc: @see #isSaved

name: sendMetadataToAllAssociatedPlayers
desc: Sends the entity metadata (DataWatcher) and attributes to all players tracking this entity, including the entity itself if a player.

name: getChunkWatcherList
desc: Returns player instances as list

name: processChunk
desc: This method currently only increases chunk inhabited time. Extension is possible in next versions

name: increaseInhabitedTime
desc: Increases chunk inhabited time every 8000 ticks

name: getItemAttributeModifiers
desc: Gets a map of item attribute modifiers, used by ItemSword to increase hit damage.

name: itemInteractionForEntity
desc: Returns true if the item can be used on the given entity, e.g. shears on sheep.

name: writeBaseAttributeMapToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagList from a BaseAttributeMap, including all its AttributeInstances

name: readAttributeModifierFromNBT
desc: Creates an AttributeModifier from an NBTTagCompound

name: writeAttributeInstanceToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagCompound from an AttributeInstance, including its AttributeModifiers

name: writeAttributeModifierToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagCompound from an AttributeModifier

name: getPathSearchRange
desc: Gets the maximum distance that the path finding will search in.

name: getAttributeModifiers
desc: Gets the attribute modifiers for this ItemStack.\nWill check for an NBT tag list containing modifiers for the stack.

name: createServerGui
desc: Creates the server GUI and sets it visible for the user.

name: getStatsComponent
desc: Generates new StatsComponent and returns it.

name: getPlayerListComponent
desc: Generates new PlayerListComponent and returns it.

name: getCurrentMoonPhaseFactor
desc: gets the current fullness of the moon expressed as a float between 1.0 and 0.0, in steps of .25

name: interactFirst
desc: First layer of player interaction

name: getMinecraftStartTimeMillis
desc: Returns the saved value of System#currentTimeMillis when the game started

name: tryTranslateKey
desc: Tries to look up a translation for the given key; spits back the key if no result was found.

name: isOnTeam
desc: Returns true if the entity is on a specific team.

name: isSameTeam
desc: Same as ==

name: addChatMessage
desc: Notifies this sender of some sort of information.  This is for messages intended to display to the user.  Used for typical output (like "you asked for whether or not this game rule is set, so here's your answer"), warnings (like "I fetched this block for you by ID, but I'd like you to know that every time you do this, I die a little inside"), and errors (like "it's not called iron_pixacke, silly").

name: isInventoryNameLocalized
desc: Returns if the inventory name is localized

name: getInventoryName
desc: Returns the name of the inventory

name: createAndLoadEntity
desc: Creates a new entity and loads its data from the specified NBT.

name: validate
desc: validates a tile entity

name: hasWorldObj
desc: Returns true if the worldObj isn't null.

name: getWorldObj
desc: Returns the worldObj for this tileEntity.

name: setWorldObj
desc: Sets the worldObj for this tileEntity.

name: getBlockType
desc: Gets the block type at the location of this entity (client-only).

name: invalidate
desc: invalidates a tile entity

name: getDescriptionPacket
desc: Overriden in a sign to provide the text.

name: clearInventory
desc: Removes all items from player inventory, including armor

name: getCurrentPlayerStrVsBlock
desc: Returns how strong the player is against the specified block at this moment

name: canHarvestBlock
desc: Checks if the player has the ability to harvest a block (checks current inventory item for a tool if necessary)

name: getGameProfile
desc: Returns the GameProfile for this player

name: saveToFile
desc: Saves this CrashReport to the given file and returns a value indicating whether we were successful at doing so.

name: isUUIDString
desc: Determines whether or not the given parameter can be parsed as a UUID.

name: tryGetUUIDFromString
desc: Parses the given string as a UUID, or returns null if the string could not be parsed.

name: joinNiceString
desc: Creates a linguistic series joining the input chat components.  Examples: 1) {} --> "",  2) {"Steve"} --> "Steve",  3) {"Steve", "Phil"} --> "Steve and Phil",  4) {"Steve", "Phil", "Mark"} --> "Steve, Phil and Mark"

name: getItemByText
desc: Gets the Item specified by the given text string.  First checks the item registry, then tries by parsing the string as an integer ID (deprecated).  Warns the sender if we matched by parsing the ID.  Throws if the item wasn't found.  Returns the item if it was found.

name: getBlockByText
desc: Gets the Block specified by the given text string.  First checks the block registry, then tries by parsing the string as an integer ID (deprecated).  Warns the sender if we matched by parsing the ID.  Throws if the block wasn't found.  Returns the block if it was found.

name: onDisconnect
desc: Invoked when disconnecting, the parameter is a ChatComponent describing the reason for termination

name: onConnectionStateTransition
desc: Allows validation of the connection state transition. Parameters: from, to (connection state). Typically throws IllegalStateException or UnsupportedOperationException if validation fails

name: onNetworkTick
desc: For scheduled network tasks. Used in NetHandlerPlayServer to send keep-alive packets and in NetHandlerLoginServer for a login-timeout

name: handleBlockChange
desc: Updates the block and metadata and generates a blockupdate (and notify the clients)

name: handleSpawnObject
desc: Spawns an instance of the objecttype indicated by the packet and sets its position and momentum

name: handleEntityStatus
desc: Invokes the entities' handleUpdateHealth method which is implemented in LivingBase (hurt/death), MinecartMobSpawner (spawn delay), FireworkRocket & MinecartTNT (explosion), IronGolem (throwing,...), Witch (spawn particles), Zombie (villager transformation), Animal (breeding mode particles), Horse (breeding/smoke particles), Sheep (...), Tameable (...), Villager (particles for breeding mode, angry and happy), Wolf (...)

name: handleSpawnPlayer
desc: Handles the creation of a nearby player entity, sets the position and held item

name: handleDestroyEntities
desc: Locally eliminates the entities. Invoked by the server when the items are in fact destroyed, or the player is no longer registered as required to monitor them. The latter  happens when distance between the player and item increases beyond a certain treshold (typically the viewing distance)

name: handleConfirmTransaction
desc: Verifies that the server and client are synchronized with respect to the inventory/container opened by the player and confirms if it is the case.

name: handleCustomPayload
desc: Handles packets that have room for a channel specification. Vanilla implemented channels are "MC|TrList" to acquire a MerchantRecipeList trades for a villager merchant, "MC|Brand" which sets the server brand? on the player instance and finally "MC|RPack" which the server uses to communicate the identifier of the default server resourcepack for the client to load.

name: handleWindowItems
desc: Handles the placement of a specified ItemStack in a specified container/inventory slot

name: handleEntityVelocity
desc: Sets the velocity of the specified entity to the specified value

name: handleWindowProperty
desc: Sets the progressbar of the opened window to the specified value

name: handleTeams
desc: Updates a team managed by the scoreboard: Create/Remove the team registration, Register/Remove the player-team-memberships, Set team displayname/prefix/suffix and/or whether friendly fire is enabled

name: handleUpdateSign
desc: Updates a specified sign with the specified text lines

name: handleUpdateScore
desc: Either updates the score with a specified value or removes the score for an objective

name: handleChat
desc: Prints a chatmessage in the chat GUI

name: handleDisconnect
desc: Closes the network channel

name: handleDisplayScoreboard
desc: Removes or sets the ScoreObjective to be displayed at a particular scoreboard position (list, sidebar, below name)

name: handleHeldItemChange
desc: Updates which hotbar slot of the player is currently selected

name: handlePlayerPosLook
desc: Handles changes in player positioning and rotation such as when travelling to a new dimension, (re)spawning, mounting horses etc. Seems to immediately reply to the server with the clients post-processing perspective on the player positioning

name: handleEntityMovement
desc: Updates the specified entity's position by the specified relative moment and absolute rotation. Note that subclassing of the packet allows for the specification of a subset of this data (e.g. only rel. position, abs. rotation or both).

name: handleBlockAction
desc: Triggers Block.onBlockEventReceived, which is implemented in BlockPistonBase for extension/retraction, BlockNote for setting the instrument (including audiovisual feedback) and in BlockContainer to set the number of players accessing a (Ender)Chest

name: handleChunkData
desc: Updates the specified chunk with the supplied data, marks it for re-rendering and lighting recalculation

name: handleMaps
desc: Updates the worlds MapStorage with the specified MapData for the specified map-identifier and invokes a MapItemRenderer for it

name: handleOpenWindow
desc: Displays a GUI by ID. In order starting from id 0: Chest, Workbench, Furnace, Dispenser, Enchanting table, Brewing stand, Villager merchant, Beacon, Anvil, Hopper, Dropper, Horse

name: handleSetSlot
desc: Handles pickin up an ItemStack or dropping one in your inventory or an open (non-creative) container

name: handleEntityHeadLook
desc: Updates the direction in which the specified entity is looking, normally this head rotation is independent of the rotation of the entity itself

name: handleSignEditorOpen
desc: Creates a sign in the specified location if it didn't exist and opens the GUI to edit its text

name: handleUpdateTileEntity
desc: Updates the NBTTagCompound metadata of instances of the following entitytypes: Mob spawners, command blocks, beacons, skulls, flowerpot

name: handleTabComplete
desc: Displays the available command-completion options the server knows of

name: handleEntityTeleport
desc: Updates an entity's position and rotation as specified by the packet

name: handleCloseWindow
desc: Resets the ItemStack held in hand and closes the window that is opened

name: handleUseBed
desc: Retrieves the player identified by the packet, puts him to sleep if possible (and flags whether all players are asleep)

name: handleAnimation
desc: Renders a specified animation: Waking up a player, a living entity swinging its currently held item, being hurt or receiving a critical hit by normal or magical means

name: handleSpawnMob
desc: Spawns the mob entity at the specified location, with the specified rotation, momentum and type. Updates the entities Datawatchers with the entity metadata specified in the packet

name: handleJoinGame
desc: Registers some server properties (gametype,hardcore-mode,terraintype,difficulty,player limit), creates a new WorldClient and sets the player initial dimension

name: handleExplosion
desc: Initiates a new explosion (sound, particles, drop spawn) for the affected blocks indicated by the packet.

name: handleEntityMetadata
desc: Invoked when the server registers new proximate objects in your watchlist or when objects in your watchlist have changed -> Registers any changes locally

name: handleSpawnExperienceOrb
desc: Spawns an experience orb and sets its value (amount of XP)

name: handleMultiBlockChange
desc: Received from the servers PlayerManager if between 1 and 64 blocks in a chunk are changed. If only one block requires an update, the server sends S23PacketBlockChange and if 64 or more blocks are changed, the server sends S21PacketChunkData

name: handleSpawnPainting
desc: Handles the spawning of a painting object

name: handleParticles
desc: Spawns a specified number of particles at the specified location with a randomized displacement according to specified bounds

name: handleEntityProperties
desc: Updates en entity's attributes and their respective modifiers, which are used for speed bonusses (player sprinting, animals fleeing, baby speed), weapon/tool attackDamage, hostiles followRange randomization, zombie maxHealth and knockback resistance as well as reinforcement spawning chance.

name: handleScoreboardObjective
desc: May create a scoreboard objective, remove an objective from the scoreboard or update an objectives' displayname

name: handleSpawnGlobalEntity
desc: Handles globally visible entities. Used in vanilla for lightning bolts

name: handleStatistics
desc: Updates the players statistics or achievements

name: handleBlockBreakAnim
desc: Updates all registered IWorldAccess instances with destroyBlockInWorldPartially

name: kickPlayerFromServer
desc: Kick a player from the server with a reason

name: handleSlashCommand
desc: Handle commands that start with a /

name: processHandshake
desc: There are two recognized intentions for initiating a handshake: logging in and acquiring server status. The NetworkManager's protocol will be reconfigured according to the specified intention, although a login-intention must pass a versioncheck or receive a disconnect otherwise

name: isAirBlock
desc: Returns true if the block at the specified coordinates is empty

name: findClosestStructure
desc: Returns the location of the closest structure of the specified type. If not found returns null.

name: destroyBlockInWorldPartially
desc: Starts (or continues) destroying a block with given ID at the given coordinates for the given partially destroyed value.

name: notifyBlockChange
desc: The block type change and need to notify other systems  Args: x, y, z, blockID

name: isBlockNormalCubeDefault
desc: Checks if the block is a solid, normal cube. If the chunk does not exist, or is not loaded, it returns the boolean parameter

name: setBlock
desc: Sets a block by a coordinate

name: scheduleBlockUpdate
desc: Used to schedule a call to the updateTick method on the specified block.

name: setBlock
desc: Sets the block ID and metadata at a given location. Args: X, Y, Z, new block ID, new metadata, flags. Flag 1 will cause a block update. Flag 2 will send the change to clients (you almost always want this). Flag 4 prevents the block from being re-rendered, if this is a client world. Flags can be added together.

name: doesBlockHaveSolidTopSurface
desc: Returns true if the block at the given coordinate has a solid (buildable) top surface.

name: createUnderlyingMap
desc: Creates the Map we will use to map keys to their registered values.

name: containsKey
desc: Does this registry contain an entry for the given key?

name: getKeys
desc: Gets all the keys recognized by this registry.

name: getNameForObject
desc: Gets the name we use to identify the given object.

name: containsID
desc: Gets a value indicating whether this registry contains an object that can be identified by the given integer value

name: getObjectForID
desc: Gets the object identified by the given ID.

name: ensureNamespaced
desc: Ensures that the given name is indicated by a colon-delimited namespace, prepending "minecraft:" if it is not already.

name: addObject
desc: Adds a new object to this registry, keyed by both the given integer ID and the given string.

name: getIDForObject
desc: Gets the integer ID we use to identify the given object.

name: readBlob
desc: Will read a byte array from the supplied ByteBuf, the first short encountered will be interpreted as the size of the byte array to read in

name: serialize
desc: Returns a string formatted as comma separated [field]=[value] values. Used by Minecraft for logging purposes.

name: hasPriority
desc: If true, the network manager will process the packet immediately when received, otherwise it will queue it for processing. Currently true for: Disconnect, LoginSuccess, KeepAlive, ServerQuery/Info, Ping/Pong

name: readPacketData
desc: Reads the raw packet data from the data stream.

name: writeBlob
desc: Will write a byte array to supplied ByteBuf as a separately defined structure by prefixing the byte array with its length

name: generatePacket
desc: Returns a packet instance, given the params: BiMap<int, (Packet) Class> and (int) id

name: writePacketData
desc: Writes the raw packet data to the data stream.

name: getExplosionResistance
desc: Returns how much this block can resist explosions from the passed in entity.

name: fillWithRain
desc: currently only used by BlockCauldron to incrament meta-data during rain

name: dropBlockAsItem_do
desc: Spawns EntityItem in the world for the given ItemStack if the world is not remote.

name: getDamageValue
desc: Get the block's damage value (for use with pick block).

name: createStackedBlock
desc: Returns an item stack containing a single instance of the current block type. 'i' is the block's subtype/damage and is ignored for blocks which do not support subtypes. Blocks which cannot be harvested should return null.

name: getRenderType
desc: The type of render function that is called for this block

name: getEnableStats
desc: Return the state of blocks statistics flags - if the block is counted for mined and placed.

name: getTickRandomly
desc: Returns whether or not this block is of a type that needs random ticking. Called for ref-counting purposes by ExtendedBlockStorage in order to broadly cull a chunk from the random chunk update list for efficiency's sake.

name: isVecInsideYZBounds
desc: Checks if a vector is within the Y and Z bounds of the block.

name: canDropFromExplosion
desc: Return whether this block can drop from an explosion.

name: isVecInsideXYBounds
desc: Checks if a vector is within the X and Y bounds of the block.

name: getBlockBoundsMinY
desc: returns the block bounderies minY value

name: getCollisionBoundingBoxFromPool
desc: Returns a bounding box from the pool of bounding boxes (this means this box can change after the pool has been cleared to be reused)

name: getBlockBoundsMaxY
desc: returns the block bounderies maxY value

name: setStepSound
desc: Sets the footstep sound for the block. Returns the object for convenience in constructing.

name: updateTick
desc: Ticks the block if it's been scheduled

name: setTickRandomly
desc: Sets whether this block type will receive random update ticks

name: canCollideCheck
desc: Returns whether this block is collideable based on the arguments passed in \n@param par1 block metaData \n@param par2 whether the player right-clicked while holding a boat

name: quantityDroppedWithBonus
desc: Returns the usual quantity dropped by the block plus a bonus of 1 to 'i' (inclusive).

name: onBlockHarvested
desc: Called when the block is attempted to be harvested

name: setBlockBoundsForItemRender
desc: Sets the block's bounds for rendering it as an item

name: isVecInsideXZBounds
desc: Checks if a vector is within the X and Z bounds of the block.

name: onBlockPlacedBy
desc: Called when the block is placed in the world.

name: dropBlockAsItemWithChance
desc: Drops the block items with a specified chance of dropping the specified items

name: damageDropped
desc: Determines the damage on the item the block drops. Used in cloth and wood.

name: getBlockBoundsMaxZ
desc: returns the block bounderies maxZ value

name: dropBlockAsItem
desc: Drops the specified block items

name: onBlockClicked
desc: Called when a player hits the block. Args: world, x, y, z, player

name: getBlockBoundsMinX
desc: returns the block bounderies minX value

name: getBlockBoundsMinZ
desc: returns the block bounderies minZ value

name: canPlaceBlockOnSide
desc: checks to see if you can place this block can be placed on that side of a block: BlockLever overrides

name: setHardness
desc: Sets how many hits it takes to break a block.

name: setLightOpacity
desc: Sets how much light is blocked going through this block. Returns the object for convenience in constructing.

name: onPostBlockPlaced
desc: Called after a block is placed

name: setLightLevel
desc: Sets the light value that the block emits. Returns resulting block instance for constructing convenience. Args: level

name: canBlockStay
desc: Can this block stay at this position.  Similar to canPlaceBlockAt except gets checked often with plants.

name: onBlockDestroyedByExplosion
desc: Called upon the block being destroyed by an explosion

name: onBlockActivated
desc: Called upon block activation (right click on the block.)

name: getLocalizedName
desc: Gets the localized name of this block. Used for the statistics page.

name: getUnlocalizedName
desc: Returns the unlocalized name of the block with "tile." appended to the front.

name: canProvidePower
desc: Can this block provide power. Only wire currently seems to have this change based on its state.

name: quantityDropped
desc: Returns the quantity of items to drop on block destruction.

name: onFallenUpon
desc: Block's chance to react to an entity falling on it.

name: setResistance
desc: Sets the the blocks resistance to explosions. Returns the object for convenience in constructing.

name: getBlockBoundsMaxX
desc: returns the block bounderies maxX value

name: isFenceGateOpen
desc: Returns if the fence gate is open according to its metadata.

name: createNewTileEntity
desc: Returns a new instance of a block's tile entity class. Called on placing the block.

name: createDeepCopy
desc: Creates a deep copy of this style.  No changes to this instance or its parent style will be reflected in the copy.

name: setChatHoverEvent
desc: Sets the event that should be run when text of this ChatStyle is hovered over.

name: getChatHoverEvent
desc: The effective chat hover event.

name: getColor
desc: Gets the effective color of this ChatStyle.

name: setItalic
desc: Sets whether or not text of this ChatStyle should be italicized.  Set to false if, e.g., the parent style is italicized and you want to override that for this style.

name: setParentStyle
desc: Sets the fallback ChatStyle to use if this ChatStyle does not override some value.  Without a parent, obvious defaults are used (bold: false, underlined: false, etc).

name: getBold
desc: Whether or not text of this ChatStyle should be in bold.

name: getParent
desc: Gets the immediate parent of this ChatStyle.

name: setStrikethrough
desc: Sets whether or not to format text of this ChatStyle using strikethrough.  Set to false if, e.g., the parent style uses strikethrough and you want to override that for this style.

name: setBold
desc: Sets whether or not text of this ChatStyle should be in bold.  Set to false if, e.g., the parent style is bold and you want text of this style to be unbolded.

name: setUnderlined
desc: Sets whether or not text of this ChatStyle should be underlined.  Set to false if, e.g., the parent style is underlined and you want to override that for this style.

name: isEmpty
desc: Whether or not this style is empty (inherits everything from the parent).

name: createShallowCopy
desc: Creates a shallow copy of this style.  Changes to this instance's values will not be reflected in the copy, but changes to the parent style's values WILL be reflected in both this instance and the copy, wherever either does not override a value.

name: getObfuscated
desc: Whether or not text of this ChatStyle should be obfuscated.

name: getUnderlined
desc: Whether or not text of this ChatStyle should be underlined.

name: getChatClickEvent
desc: The effective chat click event.

name: getStrikethrough
desc: Whether or not to format text of this ChatStyle using strikethrough.

name: setObfuscated
desc: Sets whether or not text of this ChatStyle should be obfuscated.  Set to false if, e.g., the parent style is obfuscated and you want to override that for this style.

name: setColor
desc: Sets the color for this ChatStyle to the given value.  Only use color values for this; set other values using the specific methods.

name: setChatClickEvent
desc: Sets the event that should be run when text of this ChatStyle is clicked on.

name: getItalic
desc: Whether or not text of this ChatStyle should be italicized.

name: getSiblings
desc: Gets the sibling components of this one.

name: appendSibling
desc: Appends the given component to the end of this one.

name: appendText
desc: Appends the given text to the end of this component.

name: createCopy
desc: Creates a copy of this component.  Almost a deep copy, except the style is shallow-copied.

name: getUnformattedText
desc: Gets the text of this component, without any special formatting codes added.  TODO: why is this two different methods?

name: getUnformattedTextForChat
desc: Gets the text of this component, without any special formatting codes added, for chat.  TODO: why is this two different methods?

name: createDeepCopyIterator
desc: Creates an iterator that iterates over the given components, returning deep copies of each component in turn so that the properties of the returned objects will remain externally consistent after being returned.

name: getChatComponentText_TextValue
desc: Gets the text value of this ChatComponentText.  TODO: what are getUnformattedText and getUnformattedTextForChat missing that made someone decide to create a third equivalent method that only ChatComponentText can implement?

name: initializeFromFormat
desc: initializes our children from a format string, using the format args to fill in the placeholder variables.

name: ensureInitialized
desc: ensures that our children are initialized from the most recent string translation mapping.

name: getTagList
desc: Gets the NBTTagList object with the given name. Args: name, NBTBase type

name: getCompoundTagAt
desc: Retrieves the NBTTagCompound at the specified index in the list

name: getStringTagAt
desc: Retrieves the tag String value at the specified index in the list

name: getLastUpdateTimeInMilliseconds
desc: Gets the time, in milliseconds since epoch, that this instance was last updated

name: getValue
desc: Gets the value to perform the action on when this event is raised.  For example, if the action is "open URL", this would be the URL to open.

name: getAction
desc: Gets the action to perform when this event is raised.

name: getValueByCanonicalName
desc: Gets a value by its canonical name.

name: getCanonicalName
desc: Gets the canonical name for this action (e.g., "run_command")

name: shouldAllowInChat
desc: Indicates whether this event can be run from chat text.

name: getValueByCanonicalName
desc: Gets a value by its canonical name.

name: getCanonicalName
desc: Gets the canonical name for this action (e.g., "show_achievement")

name: shouldAllowInChat
desc: Indicates whether this event can be run from chat text.

name: getAction
desc: Gets the action to perform when this event is raised.

name: getValue
desc: Gets the value to perform the action on when this event is raised.  For example, if the action is "show item", this would be the item to show.

name: closeChannel
desc: Closes the channel, the parameter can be used for an exit message (not certain how it gets sent)

name: setNetHandler
desc: Sets the NetHandler for this NetworkManager, no checks are made if this handler is suitable for the particular connection state (protocol)

name: disableAutoRead
desc: Switches the channel to manual reading modus

name: setConnectionState
desc: Sets the new connection state and registers which packets this channel may send and receive

name: isChannelOpen
desc: Returns true if this NetworkManager has an active channel, false otherwise

name: scheduleOutboundPacket
desc: Will flush the outbound queue and dispatch the supplied Packet if the channel is ready, otherwise it adds the packet to the outbound queue and registers the GenericFutureListener to fire after transmission

name: enableEncryption
desc: Adds an encoder+decoder to the channel pipeline. The parameter is the secret key used for encrypted communication

name: getNetHandler
desc: Gets the current handler for processing packets

name: getExitMessage
desc: If this channel is closed, returns the exit message, null otherwise.

name: isLocalChannel
desc: True if this NetworkManager uses a memory connection (single player game). False may imply both an active TCP connection or simply no active connection at all

name: dispatchPacket
desc: Will commit the packet to the channel. If the current thread 'owns' the channel it will write and flush the packet, otherwise it will add a task for the channel eventloop thread to do that.

name: flushOutboundQueue
desc: Will iterate through the outboundPacketQueue and dispatch all Packets

name: writeStringToBuffer
desc: Writes a (UTF-8 encoded) String to this buffer. Will throw IOException if String length exceeds 32767 bytes

name: writeNBTTagCompoundToBuffer
desc: Writes a compressed NBTTagCompound to this buffer

name: writeVarIntToBuffer
desc: Writes a compressed int to the buffer. The smallest number of bytes to fit the passed int will be written. Of each such byte only 7 bits will be used to describe the actual value since its most significant bit dictates whether the next byte is part of that same int. Micro-optimization for int values that are expected to have values below 128.

name: writeItemStackToBuffer
desc: Writes the ItemStack's ID (short), then size (byte), then damage. (short)

name: readStringFromBuffer
desc: Reads a string from this buffer. Expected parameter is maximum allowed string length. Will throw IOException if string length exceeds this value!

name: getVarIntSize
desc: Calculates the number of bytes required to fit the supplied int (0-5) if it were to be read/written using readVarIntFromBuffer or writeVarIntToBuffer

name: readItemStackFromBuffer
desc: Reads an ItemStack from this buffer

name: readVarIntFromBuffer
desc: Reads a compressed int from the buffer. To do so it maximally reads 5 byte-sized chunks whose most significant bit dictates whether another byte should be read.

name: readNBTTagCompoundFromBuffer
desc: Reads a compressed NBTTagCompound from this buffer

name: translateToFallback
desc: Translates a Stat name using the fallback (hardcoded en_US) locale.  Looks like it's only intended to be used if translateToLocal fails.

name: getLastTranslationUpdateTimeInMilliseconds
desc: Gets the time, in milliseconds since epoch, that the translation mapping was last updated

name: getSerializableElement
desc: Gets the JsonElement that can be serialized.

name: getJsonSerializableValue
desc: Gets the JsonSerializable value stored in this tuple.

name: setIntegerValue
desc: Sets this tuple's integer value to the given value.

name: getIntegerValue
desc: Gets the integer value stored in this tuple.

name: setJsonSerializableValue
desc: Sets this tuple's JsonSerializable value to the given value.

name: getJsonObjectStringFieldValue
desc: Gets the string value of the field on the JsonObject with the given name.

name: jsonObjectFieldTypeIsArray
desc: Does the given JsonObject contain an array field with the given name?

name: getJsonObjectIntegerFieldValue
desc: Gets the integer value of the field on the JsonObject with the given name.

name: jsonObjectHasNamedField
desc: Does the given JsonObject contain a field with the given name?

name: getJsonElementStringValue
desc: Gets the string value of the given JsonElement.  Expects the second parameter to be the name of the element's field if an error message needs to be thrown.

name: getJsonElementAsJsonArray
desc: Gets the given JsonElement as a JsonArray.  Expects the second parameter to be the name of the element's field if an error message needs to be thrown.

name: getElementAsJsonObject
desc: Gets the given JsonElement as a JsonObject.  Expects the second parameter to be the name of the element's field if an error message needs to be thrown.

name: getJsonObjectJsonArrayField
desc: Gets the JsonArray field on the JsonObject with the given name.

name: getJsonElementIntegerValue
desc: Gets the integer value of the given JsonElement.  Expects the second parameter to be the name of the element's field if an error message needs to be thrown.

name: getJsonElementTypeDescription
desc: Gets a human-readable description of the given JsonElement's type.  For example: "a number (4)"

name: isNullOrEmpty
desc: Returns a value indicating whether the given string is null or empty.

name: addLanEndpoint
desc: Adds a channel that listens on publicly accessible network ports

name: terminateEndpoints
desc: Shuts down all open endpoints (with immediate effect?)

name: networkTick
desc: Will try to process the packets received by each NetworkManager, gracefully manage processing failures and cleans up dead connections

name: getEventID
desc: Get the Event ID (different for each BlockID)

name: writeWatchedListToPacketBuffer
desc: Writes the list of watched objects (entity attribute of type {byte, short, int, float, string, ItemStack, ChunkCoordinates}) to the specified PacketBuffer

name: readWatchedListFromPacketBuffer
desc: Reads a list of watched objects (entity attribute of type {byte, short, int, float, string, ItemStack, ChunkCoordinates}) from the supplied PacketBuffer

name: writeWatchableObjectToPacketBuffer
desc: Writes a watchable object (entity attribute of type {byte, short, int, float, string, ItemStack, ChunkCoordinates}) to the specified PacketBuffer

name: isDamageAbsolute
desc: Whether or not the damage ignores modification by potion effects or enchantments.

name: setDamageIsAbsolute
desc: Sets a value indicating whether the damage is absolute (ignores modification by potion effects or enchantments), and also clears out hunger damage.

name: isSnooperEnabled
desc: Returns whether snooping is enabled or not.

name: canCommandSenderUseCommand
desc: Returns true if the command sender is allowed to use the given command.

name: getCommandSenderName
desc: Gets the name of this command sender (usually username, but possibly "Rcon")

name: resetLog
desc: Clears the RCon log

name: getLogContents
desc: Gets the contents of the RCon log

name: getDistance
desc: Gets the distance to the position. Args: x, y, z

name: setLocationAndAngles
desc: Sets the location and Yaw/Pitch of an entity in the world

name: getBrightness
desc: Gets how bright this entity is.

name: writeEntityToNBT
desc: (abstract) Protected helper method to write subclass entity data to NBT.

name: setFire
desc: Sets entity to burn for x amount of seconds, cannot lower amount of existing fire.

name: setBeenAttacked
desc: Sets that this entity has been attacked.

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads the entity from NBT (calls an abstract helper method to read specialized data)

name: getParts
desc: Return the Entity parts making up this Entity (currently only for dragons)

name: getEntityString
desc: Returns the string that identifies this Entity's class

name: addVelocity
desc: Adds to the current velocity of the entity. Args: x, y, z

name: isWet
desc: Checks if this entity is either in water or on an open air block in rain (used in wolves).

name: isBurning
desc: Returns true if the entity is on fire. Used by render to add the fire effect on rendering.

name: isEntityEqual
desc: Returns true if Entity argument is equal to this Entity

name: setWorld
desc: Sets the reference to the World object.

name: onEntityUpdate
desc: Gets called every tick from main Entity class

name: setSprinting
desc: Set sprinting switch for Entity.

name: getDistanceToEntity
desc: Returns the distance to the entity. Args: entity

name: getYOffset
desc: Returns the Y Offset of this entity.

name: getInventory
desc: returns the inventory of this entity (only used in EntityPlayerMP it seems)

name: readEntityFromNBT
desc: (abstract) Protected helper method to read subclass entity data from NBT.

name: isOffsetPositionInLiquid
desc: Checks if the offset position from the entity's current position is inside of liquid. Args: x, y, z

name: writeToNBTOptional
desc: Either write this entity to the NBT tag given and return true, or return false without doing anything. If this returns false the entity is not saved on disk. Ridden entities return false here as they are saved with their rider.

name: getLookVec
desc: returns a (normalized) vector of where this entity is looking

name: canTriggerWalking

name: getMountedYOffset
desc: Returns the Y offset from the entity's position for any entity riding this one.

name: setOnFireFromLava
desc: Called whenever the entity is walking inside of lava.

name: getBoundingBox
desc: returns the bounding box for this entity

name: newFloatNBTList
desc: Returns a new NBTTagList filled with the specified floats

name: isSprinting
desc: Get if the Entity is sprinting.

name: setFlag
desc: Enable or disable a entity flag, see getEntityFlag to read the know flags.

name: isInsideOfMaterial
desc: Checks if the current block the entity is within of the specified material type

name: handleLavaMovement
desc: Whether or not the current entity is in lava

name: moveFlying
desc: Used in both water and by flying objects

name: setCurrentItemOrArmor

name: setInPortal
desc: Called by portal blocks when an entity is within it.

name: extinguish
desc: Removes fire from entity.

name: canBeCollidedWith
desc: Returns true if other Entities should be prevented from moving through this Entity.

name: getDistanceSqToEntity
desc: Returns the squared distance to the entity. Args: entity

name: fall

name: onUpdate
desc: Called to update the entity's position/logic.

name: handleWaterMovement
desc: Returns if this entity is in water and will end up adding the waters velocity to the entity

name: onKillEntity
desc: This method gets called when the entity kills another one.

name: canAttackWithItem
desc: If returns false, the item will not inflict any damage against entities.

name: kill
desc: sets the dead flag. Used when you fall off the bottom of the world.

name: onStruckByLightning
desc: Called when a lightning bolt hits the entity.

name: mountEntity
desc: Called when a player mounts an entity. e.g. mounts a pig, mounts a boat.

name: setPositionAndRotation
desc: Sets the entity's position and rotation. Args: posX, posY, posZ, yaw, pitch

name: dealFireDamage
desc: Will deal the specified amount of damage to the entity if the entity isn't immune to fire damage. Args: amountDamage

name: getFlag

name: addToPlayerScore

name: interact
desc: Called when a player interacts with a mob. e.g. gets milk from a cow, gets into the saddle on a pig.

name: newDoubleNBTList
desc: creates a NBT list from the array of doubles passed to this function

name: isEntityAlive
desc: Checks whether target entity is alive.

name: isInWater
desc: Checks if this entity is inside water (if inWater field is true as a result of handleWaterMovement() returning true)

name: moveEntity
desc: Tries to moves the entity by the passed in displacement. Args: x, y, z

name: getDistanceSq
desc: Gets the squared distance to the position. Args: x, y, z

name: isSneaking
desc: Returns if this entity is sneaking.

name: isEntityInsideOpaqueBlock
desc: Checks if this entity is inside of an opaque block

name: setSneaking
desc: Sets the sneaking flag.

name: attackEntityFrom
desc: Called when the entity is attacked.

name: updateRidden
desc: Handles updating while being ridden by an entity

name: entityDropItem
desc: Drops an item at the position of the entity.

name: onCollideWithPlayer
desc: Called by a player entity when they collide with an entity

name: setRotation
desc: Sets the rotation of the entity. Args: yaw, pitch (both in degrees)

name: canBePushed
desc: Returns true if this entity should push and be pushed by other entities when colliding.

name: setSize
desc: Sets the width and height of the entity. Args: width, height

name: setDead
desc: Will get destroyed next tick.

name: setPosition
desc: Sets the x,y,z of the entity from the given parameters. Also seems to set up a bounding box.

name: applyEntityCollision
desc: Applies a velocity to each of the entities pushing them away from each other. Args: entity

name: writeToNBT
desc: Save the entity to NBT (calls an abstract helper method to write extra data)

name: setInWeb
desc: Sets the Entity inside a web block.

name: getCollisionBox
desc: Returns a boundingBox used to collide the entity with other entities and blocks. This enables the entity to be pushable on contact, like boats or minecarts.

name: isRiding
desc: Returns true if the entity is riding another entity, used by render to rotate the legs to be in 'sit' position for players.

name: onImpact
desc: Called when this EntityThrowable hits a block or entity.

name: getGravityVelocity
desc: Gets the amount of gravity to apply to the thrown entity with each tick.

name: setThrowableHeading
desc: Similar to setArrowHeading, it's point the throwable entity to a x, y, z direction.

name: getPotionDamage

name: moveTowards

name: onImpact

name: getIsCritical
desc: Whether the arrow has a stream of critical hit particles flying behind it.

name: setIsCritical
desc: Whether the arrow has a stream of critical hit particles flying behind it.

name: setTimeSinceHit
desc: Sets the time to count down from since the last time entity was hit.

name: setDamageTaken
desc: Sets the damage taken from the last hit.

name: getForwardDirection
desc: Gets the forward direction of the entity.

name: getTimeSinceHit
desc: Gets the time since the last hit.

name: setForwardDirection
desc: Sets the forward direction of the entity.

name: getDamageTaken
desc: Gets the damage taken from the last hit.

name: setAgeToCreativeDespawnTime
desc: sets the age of the item so that it'll despawn one minute after it has been dropped (instead of five). Used when items are dropped from players in creative mode

name: combineItems
desc: Tries to merge this item with the item passed as the parameter. Returns true if successful. Either this item or the other item will  be removed from the world.

name: onInventoryChanged
desc: Called when an the contents of an Inventory change, usually

name: getInventoryStackLimit
desc: Returns the maximum stack size for a inventory slot. Seems to always be 64, possibly will be extended. *Isn't this more of a set than a get?*

name: decrStackSize
desc: Removes from an inventory slot (first arg) up to a specified number (second arg) of items and returns them in a new stack.

name: setInventorySlotContents
desc: Sets the given item stack to the specified slot in the inventory (can be crafting or armor sections).

name: isUseableByPlayer
desc: Do not make give this method the name canInteractWith because it clashes with Container

name: getStackInSlot
desc: Returns the stack in slot i

name: getSizeInventory
desc: Returns the number of slots in the inventory.

name: getStackInSlotOnClosing
desc: When some containers are closed they call this on each slot, then drop whatever it returns as an EntityItem - like when you close a workbench GUI.

name: decrementAnimations
desc: Decrement the number of animations remaining. Only called on client side. This is used to handle the animation of receiving a block.

name: getTotalArmorValue
desc: Based on the damage values and maximum damage values of each armor item, returns the current armor value.

name: hasItemStack
desc: Returns true if the specified ItemStack exists in the inventory.

name: storeItemStack
desc: stores an itemstack in the users inventory

name: dropAllItems
desc: Drop all armor and main inventory items.

name: armorItemInSlot
desc: returns a player armor item (as itemstack) contained in specified armor slot.

name: addItemStackToInventory
desc: Adds the item stack to the inventory, returns false if it is impossible.

name: writeToNBT

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads from the given tag list and fills the slots in the inventory with the correct items.

name: getFirstEmptyStack
desc: Returns the first item stack that is empty.

name: getCurrentItem
desc: Returns the item stack currently held by the player.

name: damageArmor

name: getHotbarSize

name: storePartialItemStack

name: copyInventory

name: getStackInRowAndColumn

name: inventoryResetNeededOnSlotChange

name: getDamage

name: setDamage

name: getRollingDirection

name: setRollingDirection
desc: Sets the rolling direction the cart rolls while being attacked. Can be 1 or -1.

name: getRollingAmplitude
desc: Gets the rolling amplitude the cart rolls while being attacked.

name: setRollingAmplitude
desc: Sets the rolling amplitude the cart rolls while being attacked.

name: onValidSurface
desc: checks to make sure painting can be placed there

name: getXpValue

name: getXPSplit
desc: Get a fragment of the maximum experience points value for the supplied value of experience points value.

name: getSoundVolume
desc: Returns the volume for the sounds this mob makes.

name: getCanSpawnHere
desc: Checks if the entity's current position is a valid location to spawn this entity.

name: isPlayerSleeping
desc: Returns whether player is sleeping or not

name: onDeathUpdate

name: isMovementBlocked

name: moveEntityWithHeading

name: setAttackTarget

name: faceEntity

name: getTalkInterval
desc: Get number of ticks, at least during which the living entity will be silent.

name: dropFewItems

name: updateAITick

name: isChild

name: setPositionAndUpdate

name: getEntitySenses
desc: returns the EntitySenses Object for the EntityLiving

name: onLivingUpdate

name: getAttackTarget
desc: Gets the active target the Task system uses for tracking

name: getLivingSound

name: getMaxSpawnedInChunk
desc: Will return how many at most can spawn in a chunk at once.

name: playLivingSound
desc: Plays living's sound at its position

name: onDeath
desc: Called when the mob's health reaches 0.

name: getVerticalFaceSpeed

name: getSoundPitch

name: isAIEnabled

name: knockBack

name: applyArmorCalculations

name: spawnExplosionParticle

name: getTotalArmorValue

name: setAIMoveSpeed

name: isEntityUndead

name: updateRotation

name: getCreatureAttribute

name: applyPotionDamageCalculations
desc: Reduces damage, depending on potions

name: getDeathSound

name: getLook

name: decreaseAirSupply

name: isPlayer
desc: Only use is to identify if class is an instance of player for experience dropping

name: canEntityBeSeen

name: canAttackClass
desc: Returns true if this entity can attack entities of the specified class.

name: getAIMoveSpeed
desc: the movespeed used for the new AI system

name: addPotionEffect

name: heal

name: canDespawn

name: getExperiencePoints

name: getHeldItem

name: getEntityToAttack
